Job description
Job Summary
This role is responsible for defining, planning, and executing the product strategy, collaborating with various teams to deliver software solutions that delight customers and meet business goals. The role plans and manages technical programs or projects, effectively steering them to meet specific roadmap and feature objectives. The role develops a comprehensive software vision and roadmap for product initiatives.

A large portion of the duties of this role will be performing as ITSM ServiceNow capabilities and Business Process Engineer (BPE).

As ITSM ServiceNow capabilities lead - you will be in charge of defining & designing new capabilities/services that will be developed on HP Services ITSM platform. At the core of this job, grooming user stories, worming with Architects and development teams to ensure a good understanding of the capabilities requested, validate/test stories, drive adoption/management of change.

Once the capability is in operation, you will be in charge of enhancements as well as deep technical expertise support.

The process engineering role involves thinking process. BPEs draws inferences from process details and link these inferences to the big picture by considering business objectives in identifying process improvements and the creation of new processes.A Business Process Engineer typically has the ability to structure a large amount of information within a process framework.

In fact, the BPE will work with the Global Service Delivery team , engage with other services organizations and other HPI entities (RBUs/GBUs) to find the best way to design new digital workflows that will translate into a set of capabilities in HP ITSM ; as well solve existing service delivery agent and workflow process-related problems. This will often involve analysing existing processes and designing improved ones. BPE will be required to interpret business requirements, holding meetings, researching processes, collecting data, analyzing information and performing related tasks.

Next, to the BPE responsibilities, the individual must be able to act as a Project/Program Manager, providing direction to team activities and facilitates information validation and team decision-making process. The projects are usually cross-organizational - affecting two or three Business Units. Aside from that, The individual will need to coordinate and integrate the work efforts and deliverables of a multi-function project team related to the execution of complex projects within the Managed Services business of HP Inc.

Responsibilities

Leads through the entire product development cycle, ensuring quality and delivery.
Collaborates closely with engineering, design, and other relevant teams to ensure the successful development and delivery of high-quality software solutions on time and within scope.
Strategically partners with stakeholders to understand needs and processes
Translates complex market and stakeholder needs into product requirements and definitions.
Translates customer feedback and assesses the external environment to identify potential changes that could enhance the differentiated product roadmap.
Provides thought leadership to stakeholders to guide feature development and prioritization.
Translates user requirements into executable and workable feature items with the software engineering team.
Provides guidance for junior team members on product management strategies.
Tracks and reports key metrics to drive future product developments.
Advises key stakeholders on the portfolio strategy across all phases of the lifecycle.
SME on HP ITSM ServiceNow capabilities - deep understanding of workflows, fundamental data and possible configurations
Write stories for future capabilities development, Run Test, Plan for enhancements
Education & Experience Recommended

Four-year or Graduate Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Systems, or any other related discipline or commensurate work experience or demonstrated competence.
Typically has 7-10 years of work experience, preferably in product management, digital or software product development, or a related field.
