Product Manager
Bangalore
The Product Manager is accountable for the value delivery of the product to the business. He or she collaborates with the Product Owner to set the
product vision, brings forward the best technology/solutions to solve business problems (e.g. technology and innovation funnels), co[1]creates the
product roadmap and success metrics, fulfills the product lifecycle within Enterprise compliance and controls framework, creates value delivery
through product development, performs financial management, and sets the right product environment and mindset for the product team.
• Sets the direction for the product line aligned to business vision and agreed KPIs
• Manages senior level stakeholders for the product across RDS to ensure tight orchestration,
early warning on new requirements and early warning on potential unmet needs and
problems.
• Provides technology/innovation advisory towards lines of businesses that the product line
supports to ensure that right innovative technologies are offered as possible ideas to solve
complex business problems
• Builds and leads the product teams under the product line
• Promotes design thinking, agile and lean start up to create MVPs within the product line • Focuses on maximizing the adoption of high-impact digitalization
• Finds the optimal adoption mix of new and emerging propositions vs tried and tested capabilities
• Accelerates maturation and replication of the available digital technology propositions at scale
• Guides product line build or buy decisions and enables the process of investment decision[1]making across products within the product line
• Drives fulfilment of the product lifecycle across the product line through teams of properly
skilled product managers and multi-disciplinary teams. Own and drive the delivery plan in
line with the product lifecycle aligning with other PLMs within the IT business portfolio to
assure lean product development across the full product value stream and fulfilment of the
target IT Strategic Plan.
• Drives rigour in KPI fulfilment through investment discipline across the product lifecycle by
product managers within the product line. Aggregate reporting for the product line through
available IT business management tools transparency of product line performance against
agreed critical success factors.
• Elevates product manager awareness and compliance to agreed Enterprise technology and
data standards, acting as escalation point in instances of divergence for avoidance of
technical debt.
• Works tightly with IT Managers and other Product Line Managers across the IT business
portfolio to enable the agreed business face-up model and drive alignment on Business IT
approaches towards other IT functional lines and into the business across the product
lifecycle. Speak as confidently to technical teams about product development as to
commercial stakeholders about complex product line challenges.
• Demonstrates deep understanding of and proximity to business owners and consumers of
the product line's outputs (internal and/or external). Drive heavy use of business owner and
consumer insights to inform product vision and actionable roadmaps, bringing additional
business domain knowledge and external perspectives into products within the product line.
• Champions use of product data and aggregated product line insights across respective
product roadmaps within the product line.
• Builds, leads, and inspires a team to deliver the Product roadmap against the prevailing
lifecycle, sourcing capability from across the organisation. Focus actions against product
attributes of desirability, feasibility, and viability.
• Manages the product team of their day-to-day delivery accountabilities
